UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Sarah Mitchell is a board-certified cardiologist with over 12 years of experience in preventive cardiology and heart failure management. She completed her fellowship at Johns Hopkins Hospital and has since dedicated her career to helping patients understand and manage cardiovascular risk factors before they become life-threatening. Dr. Mitchell takes a holistic approach to heart health, combining evidence-based medicine with lifestyle interventions including nutrition counseling and stress management techniques. She is a published researcher with contributions to leading cardiology journals, and regularly presents at international cardiology conferences. Her patients appreciate her clear communication style and her ability to explain complex cardiac conditions in simple, actionable terms. She is fluent in English and Spanish and welcomes patients from diverse backgrounds.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Hans Weber is a highly respected neurologist based in Berlin, specializing in headache disorders and multiple sclerosis. He trained at the Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich, one of Europe''s premier medical institutions, and completed advanced subspecialty training in neuroimmunology in Vienna. With eight years of clinical experience, Dr. Weber has helped thousands of patients regain quality of life through personalized migraine management plans and cutting-edge MS therapies. He is passionate about patient education and believes that informed patients achieve better outcomes. Dr. Weber is an active member of the European Academy of Neurology and contributes regularly to peer-reviewed publications on demyelinating diseases. He conducts consultations in both German and English, ensuring patients always feel fully understood and supported throughout their treatment journey.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Priya Sharma is a distinguished dermatologist with 15 years of expertise spanning both medical and cosmetic dermatology, with a particular passion for early skin cancer detection and prevention. She graduated top of her class from AIIMS New Delhi and completed postdoctoral training at the University of London. Dr. Sharma employs the latest dermoscopy techniques and digital skin mapping technology to detect malignant changes at the earliest possible stage, significantly improving patient outcomes. Beyond oncology, she offers comprehensive care for acne, eczema, rosacea, and psoriasis. Patients describe her consultations as thorough and compassionate, with an emphasis on long-term skin health rather than quick fixes. She regularly volunteers in rural dermatology outreach programs and lectures at medical colleges throughout India. She consults in Hindi and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. James Okafor is a dedicated general practitioner with a decade of experience providing comprehensive primary care across diverse patient populations in Lagos and internationally. He holds an MBBS from the University of Ibadan and an MSc in Public Health from the London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine. Dr. Okafor is deeply committed to preventive medicine and patient education, firmly believing that most chronic diseases can be significantly delayed or prevented through early intervention and lifestyle change. He provides thorough annual health assessments, chronic disease management, and health coaching tailored to each patient''s unique circumstances. Outside the clinic, he volunteers with community health initiatives targeting hypertension and diabetes awareness. He speaks English, French, and Yoruba, making him accessible to a wide range of patients across West Africa and beyond.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Mei Chen is a compassionate psychiatrist based in Shanghai with seven years of clinical experience helping patients navigate anxiety disorders, depression, and trauma. She trained at Fudan University School of Medicine and completed a fellowship in cognitive behavioral therapy at the University of Toronto. Dr. Chen integrates evidence-based psychotherapeutic approaches with pharmacological management, creating individualized treatment plans that address both the biological and psychological dimensions of mental health. She is a strong advocate for reducing mental health stigma, particularly within East Asian communities, and frequently writes about this topic in medical and public health publications. Her patients consistently describe her as warm, non-judgmental, and highly effective at creating a safe space for open dialogue. She conducts sessions in Mandarin and English and offers flexible scheduling for international patients across time zones.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Carlos Mendez is an experienced orthopedic surgeon and sports medicine specialist based in Mexico City, with 14 years of practice focused on helping athletes and active individuals recover from musculoskeletal injuries and return to peak performance. He trained at the Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México and completed sports medicine fellowships in both the United States and Spain. Dr. Mendez has served as the team physician for several professional football clubs and national athletics teams, giving him unparalleled expertise in high-performance sports injuries. He offers comprehensive consultation for joint pain, ligament injuries, tendinopathies, and post-surgical rehabilitation. His approach emphasizes conservative management wherever possible, reserving surgical intervention for cases where it offers clear benefit. He communicates fluently in Spanish, English, and Portuguese, ensuring all his patients receive care in their preferred language.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Amina Hassan is a highly skilled gynecologist with 11 years of experience specializing in reproductive health, minimally invasive gynecological surgery, and women''s wellness throughout all life stages. She completed her medical degree at Cairo University and her subspecialty training in laparoscopic surgery at the University of Amsterdam. Dr. Hassan is known for her meticulous surgical technique and her deeply empathetic bedside manner, which puts even the most anxious patients at ease. She provides care for a wide spectrum of conditions including polycystic ovary syndrome, fibroids, endometriosis, and complex menstrual disorders. She is also an advocate for informed reproductive choices, providing comprehensive counseling on contraception and fertility options. Dr. Hassan consults in Arabic, English, and French, and is particularly committed to providing culturally sensitive care for patients from the Middle East and North Africa.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000007';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Lucas Silva is a warm and dedicated pediatrician based in São Paulo with nine years of experience caring for children from newborns through adolescence. He graduated from the Universidade de São Paulo School of Medicine and completed his pediatric residency at Hospital das Clínicas, one of Brazil''s largest and most respected teaching hospitals. Dr. Silva has a special interest in childhood developmental milestones, vaccination programs, and the management of allergic conditions including asthma and food allergies. He takes a family-centered approach to care, recognizing that supporting parents and caregivers is just as important as treating the child. He is known for his calm demeanor and his remarkable ability to build rapport with even the shyest young patients. Dr. Silva is fluent in Portuguese, English, and Spanish, and regularly participates in pediatric health outreach programs in underserved communities.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000008';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Yuki Tanaka is a leading dermatologist based in Tokyo with 13 years of clinical experience and a subspecialty focus on autoimmune skin conditions, eczema management, and contact dermatitis. She trained at Keio University School of Medicine and conducted postdoctoral research at the University of California San Francisco, where she contributed to landmark studies on atopic dermatitis pathophysiology. Dr. Tanaka employs a rigorous diagnostic approach, using advanced patch testing and immunological workup to identify triggers and design targeted treatment protocols. She is particularly skilled at managing treatment-resistant cases that have not responded to conventional therapies, offering patients options that include biologics and immunomodulatory agents. Her publications have been cited widely in international dermatology literature. Dr. Tanaka consults in Japanese and English and is deeply committed to improving quality of life for patients with chronic inflammatory skin conditions.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000009';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Elena Popescu is a neurologist based in Bucharest with six years of focused clinical experience in epilepsy management and movement disorders including Parkinson''s disease and essential tremor. She holds her medical degree from Carol Davila University of Medicine and completed advanced neurology training at the University of Lyon in France. Dr. Popescu takes a multidisciplinary approach to neurological care, collaborating closely with physiotherapists, speech therapists, and neuropsychologists to provide comprehensive support for her patients. She is an enthusiastic adopter of telemedicine, recognizing its potential to bring high-quality neurological care to patients in rural and underserved areas of Eastern Europe. Her patients appreciate her thorough explanations and her willingness to explore all available therapeutic options before escalating treatment. She consults fluently in Romanian, English, and French.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Omar Faruk is an interventional cardiologist with 16 years of experience in diagnosing and treating complex coronary artery disease and acute cardiac events. He trained at Dhaka Medical College and completed his interventional cardiology fellowship at Hammersmith Hospital in London. Dr. Faruk is highly skilled in coronary angioplasty, stent placement, and structural heart interventions, having performed over two thousand procedures throughout his career. He is deeply committed to making high-quality cardiac care accessible in South Asia, where cardiovascular disease rates are rising sharply. In addition to his clinical work, Dr. Faruk supervises cardiology trainees and contributes to medical education initiatives across Bangladesh. He has a particular interest in the intersection of diabetes and heart disease and offers integrated management programs for patients with both conditions. He consults in Arabic and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Sofia Greco is a compassionate and experienced psychiatrist based in Rome with a decade of clinical practice specializing in trauma, post-traumatic stress disorder, and complex mood disorders. She completed her psychiatry residency at the University of Rome La Sapienza and pursued additional training in trauma-focused cognitive behavioral therapy and EMDR at institutes in Switzerland and the United Kingdom. Dr. Greco has extensive experience working with survivors of acute trauma, refugees, and individuals navigating grief and loss. She adopts an integrative treatment model that combines psychotherapy with careful pharmacological management, always prioritizing the patient''s long-term wellbeing over short-term symptom suppression. She is a founding member of a Rome-based trauma support network and regularly supervises junior psychiatrists. She consults in Italian, English, and French, creating an inclusive and safe environment for patients from across Europe.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. David Kim is a highly trained orthopedic specialist based in Seoul with 18 years of surgical experience focusing on complex spine conditions and spinal rehabilitation. He graduated from Seoul National University College of Medicine, consistently ranked among Asia''s top medical institutions, and completed fellowships in spinal surgery at the Cleveland Clinic and the University of Tokyo. Dr. Kim is renowned for his expertise in minimally invasive spinal surgery techniques, which significantly reduce recovery times and postoperative pain compared to traditional open procedures. He treats a broad spectrum of conditions including herniated discs, spinal stenosis, scoliosis, and degenerative disc disease. His rehabilitation programs are individualized and evidence-based, combining surgical outcomes with structured physiotherapy. Dr. Kim has trained surgeons from across Asia and regularly presents his research at international spine surgery congresses. He consults in Korean and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000013';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Fatima Malik is a dedicated family medicine physician based in Karachi with eight years of experience providing holistic, patient-centered primary care to individuals and families across all age groups. She trained at Aga Khan University, one of Pakistan''s most prestigious medical institutions, and holds additional qualifications in lifestyle medicine from the Royal College of General Practitioners in London. Dr. Malik believes strongly in treating the whole person rather than isolated symptoms, incorporating mental health, nutrition, sleep, and social determinants of health into every consultation. She is particularly skilled in the management of type 2 diabetes, hypertension, and thyroid disorders, which are highly prevalent in her patient population. She is known for her patience, warmth, and her ability to build lasting therapeutic relationships with her patients and their families. She consults in Urdu, English, and Arabic.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000014';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Andrei Volkov is one of Russia''s most experienced cardiologists with two decades of specialized practice in cardiac electrophysiology and the management of complex heart rhythm disorders. He trained at the First Moscow State Medical University and completed advanced electrophysiology training at the Heart Rhythm Institute in Oklahoma City. Dr. Volkov has performed over three thousand electrophysiology studies and catheter ablation procedures, achieving outcomes that consistently exceed national benchmarks. He treats a wide range of arrhythmias including atrial fibrillation, supraventricular tachycardia, and ventricular arrhythmias, and has particular expertise in the management of patients with implantable cardiac devices such as pacemakers and defibrillators. He is the author of two textbook chapters on atrial fibrillation management and has mentored dozens of electrophysiology trainees over his career. He consults in Russian and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000015';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Nina Johansson is a specialist pediatrician based in Stockholm with 12 years of experience focusing on childhood developmental disorders, behavioral health, and neurodiversity. She trained at the Karolinska Institute, one of the world''s leading medical universities, and pursued subspecialty training in developmental pediatrics at Great Ormond Street Hospital in London. Dr. Johansson has extensive experience diagnosing and supporting children with ADHD, autism spectrum disorder, dyslexia, and anxiety-related conditions. She works closely with educational psychologists, speech therapists, and school counselors to ensure children receive coordinated, holistic support across all areas of their lives. Her approach is always strengths-based, helping families recognize and build on what their child does well. She is a published author on early intervention strategies for developmental disorders. She consults in Swedish, English, and Norwegian.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000016';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Kwame Asante is a versatile general practitioner based in Accra with nine years of clinical experience and a specialist interest in tropical medicine, infectious diseases, and travel health. He holds an MBChB from the University of Ghana Medical School and a diploma in Tropical Medicine and Hygiene from the Liverpool School of Tropical Medicine. Dr. Asante provides comprehensive primary care while offering specialized consultations for patients with malaria, typhoid, tuberculosis, and other regionally prevalent infections. He also runs a busy travel medicine clinic, advising international travelers on vaccination requirements, malaria prophylaxis, and health precautions for travel to high-risk destinations. He is an active contributor to Ghana Health Service guidelines on infectious disease management and has participated in multiple WHO-supported outbreak response missions. He consults fluently in English, Twi, and French.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000017';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Isabelle Dupont is a highly experienced obstetrician and gynecologist based in Paris with 14 years of practice specializing in high-risk pregnancies, assisted reproductive technologies, and complex gynecological conditions. She trained at Pierre and Marie Curie University School of Medicine in Paris and completed subspecialty training in maternal-fetal medicine at Hôpital Necker. Dr. Dupont has guided hundreds of high-risk pregnancies to successful outcomes, managing conditions including preeclampsia, gestational diabetes, multiple gestations, and preterm labor with exceptional skill and care. She is also a recognized expert in IVF preparation and fertility preservation, working closely with reproductive endocrinologists to support patients on their journey to parenthood. Her consultations are known for their thoroughness, warmth, and respect for each patient''s individual circumstances and values. She consults in French and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000018';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Rafael Torres is a skilled dermatologist based in Bogotá with seven years of experience and a subspecialty focus on hair and scalp disorders, including androgenetic alopecia, alopecia areata, and scarring alopecias. He trained at the Universidad Nacional de Colombia and completed an international fellowship in trichology and hair restoration at the Universidad Complutense de Madrid. Dr. Torres employs a thorough diagnostic approach combining dermoscopic scalp analysis, trichoscopy, and targeted laboratory investigations to identify the root cause of each patient''s hair loss before designing a personalized treatment plan. He offers both medical and procedural treatments including platelet-rich plasma therapy and hair transplant consultation and referral. Dr. Torres is passionate about the psychological impact of hair loss and ensures his patients receive both medical and emotional support throughout their treatment journey. He consults in Spanish, English, and Portuguese.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000019';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Aisha Diallo is a child and adolescent psychiatrist based in Dakar with 11 years of experience specializing in neurodevelopmental disorders, childhood trauma, and the unique mental health challenges facing young people in sub-Saharan Africa. She trained at Cheikh Anta Diop University and completed advanced training in child psychiatry at the University of Montreal. Dr. Diallo has pioneered culturally adapted mental health interventions that integrate traditional community support structures with evidence-based psychiatric practice, significantly improving engagement and outcomes in populations that are often resistant to conventional mental health services. She advises the Senegalese Ministry of Health on child mental health policy and has contributed to WHO guidelines on mental health in low-resource settings. She is a compassionate and dedicated clinician who believes every child deserves the chance to thrive. She consults in French, English, and Wolof.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000020';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Peter Novak is a neurologist based in Prague with 15 years of focused clinical and research experience in stroke prevention and cerebrovascular diseases. He trained at Charles University Faculty of Medicine and completed fellowship training in vascular neurology at University College London. Dr. Novak runs a dedicated stroke prevention clinic where he identifies and aggressively manages modifiable risk factors including hypertension, atrial fibrillation, hyperlipidemia, and diabetes in patients who have suffered a TIA or minor stroke. His early intervention approach has demonstrably reduced secondary stroke rates in his patient cohort. He is a principal investigator on several multinational clinical trials examining novel anticoagulants and neuroprotective agents. Dr. Novak is also a passionate medical educator, supervising neurology residents at Motol University Hospital. He consults in Czech, English, and Slovak, and actively supports cross-border telemedicine initiatives in Central Europe.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000021';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Lena Fischer is a cardiologist based in Vienna with ten years of experience and a subspecialty focus on congenital heart disease in adults, a growing and often underserved patient population as more children with complex cardiac malformations survive into adulthood. She trained at the Medical University of Vienna and completed subspecialty training in adult congenital heart disease at the German Heart Centre in Munich. Dr. Fischer provides comprehensive longitudinal care for adults living with conditions such as atrial and ventricular septal defects, tetralogy of Fallot, transposition of the great arteries, and complex single-ventricle physiology. She collaborates closely with cardiac surgeons, electrophysiologists, and obstetricians to manage the multifaceted health needs of this complex patient group. She is a member of the European Society of Cardiology''s working group on grown-up congenital heart disease. She consults in German and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000022';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Samuel Osei is a conscientious primary care physician based in Accra with six years of experience providing accessible, high-quality healthcare to patients managing chronic conditions including hypertension, type 2 diabetes, asthma, and chronic kidney disease. He trained at the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology School of Medicine and has since built a reputation for meticulous follow-up care and his ability to help patients achieve meaningful improvements in their health markers through a combination of medication optimization and practical lifestyle counseling. Dr. Osei believes strongly that primary care is the backbone of any functioning health system, and he is committed to making chronic disease management achievable and sustainable for patients at all income levels. He is currently pursuing a postgraduate diploma in health informatics to better leverage digital health tools for his patients. He consults in English and Twi.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000023';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Valentina Russo is a specialist gynecologist based in Rome with 13 years of clinical experience dedicated to the diagnosis and management of endometriosis, chronic pelvic pain, and complex benign gynecological conditions. She trained at the University of Bologna and completed advanced laparoscopic surgery training at the World Endometriosis Society Centre of Excellence in Milan. Dr. Russo is one of Italy''s leading voices on the underdiagnosis and undertreatment of endometriosis, and has contributed to national awareness campaigns aimed at reducing the average diagnostic delay for this condition from seven years to under two. She offers thorough, empathetic consultations that validate her patients'' experiences and provide them with clear, evidence-based management options ranging from hormonal therapy to advanced excision surgery. She consults in Italian, English, and French, and welcomes international patients seeking specialist second opinions.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000024';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Ali Hassan is a psychiatrist based in Beirut with nine years of experience specializing in addiction medicine, substance use disorders, and the dual diagnosis of addiction with underlying psychiatric conditions such as depression, anxiety, and PTSD. He trained at the American University of Beirut Faculty of Medicine, renowned for its rigorous American-standard medical education, and completed addiction psychiatry training at McLean Hospital, Harvard Medical School. Dr. Hassan takes a compassionate, non-judgmental approach to addiction, recognizing it as a complex brain disease rather than a moral failing. He provides comprehensive assessment and individualized treatment plans incorporating medication-assisted treatment, motivational interviewing, and evidence-based psychotherapy. He has worked extensively with populations affected by conflict-related trauma and its relationship to substance misuse. He consults in Arabic, English, and French.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000025';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Marie Leblanc is a highly experienced pediatrician based in Montreal with 17 years of specialized practice in neonatal care and the developmental follow-up of premature infants. She trained at McGill University Faculty of Medicine and completed a neonatology fellowship at the Hospital for Sick Children in Toronto. Dr. Leblanc has cared for hundreds of extremely premature infants in the neonatal intensive care unit and has a particular passion for their long-term neurodevelopmental outcomes. She runs a dedicated premature infant follow-up clinic that monitors development, identifies emerging challenges early, and coordinates intervention services to give each child the best possible start in life. She works closely with families throughout this often emotionally challenging journey, providing them with clear information, emotional support, and practical guidance. She consults in French and English and is deeply committed to family-integrated care models.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000026';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Chen Wei is one of China''s most respected neurologists with 22 years of experience specializing in dementia, Alzheimer''s disease, and cognitive neurology. He trained at Peking Union Medical College, China''s most prestigious medical institution, and completed research fellowships at the University of California San Francisco Memory and Aging Center and University College London. Dr. Wei has been at the forefront of dementia research in China, contributing to large-scale epidemiological studies that have shaped national dementia care policy. He provides comprehensive cognitive assessments, early diagnosis of neurodegenerative conditions, and personalized management plans that maximize quality of life for both patients and their caregivers. He is a strong advocate for caregiver support and runs a monthly education program for families navigating dementia care. He consults in Mandarin and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000027';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Grace Adeyemi is an orthopedic surgeon based in Lagos with 11 years of experience specializing in knee and hip replacement surgery and the management of degenerative joint disease. She trained at the University of Lagos College of Medicine and completed arthroplasty fellowship training at the Royal National Orthopaedic Hospital in London and the Hospital for Special Surgery in New York. Dr. Adeyemi has performed over fifteen hundred joint replacement procedures and is known for her precision, excellent patient outcomes, and low complication rates. She employs modern minimally invasive surgical techniques and enhanced recovery protocols that allow most of her patients to be walking within hours of surgery. Beyond the operating theatre, she is passionate about making orthopaedic care more accessible in Nigeria and has established a charitable program providing subsidized joint replacements for low-income patients. She consults in English, Yoruba, and Igbo.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000028';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Marco Ferrari is a cardiologist based in Milan with 16 years of experience and a subspecialty focus on cardiac imaging, echocardiography, and the non-invasive assessment of complex structural heart disease. He trained at the University of Milan and completed advanced cardiac imaging fellowships at the Mayo Clinic and the National Heart and Lung Institute in London. Dr. Ferrari is recognized internationally for his expertise in three-dimensional echocardiography and cardiac MRI, techniques that provide unparalleled detail about cardiac structure and function without exposing patients to radiation. He performs comprehensive imaging assessments for patients with valvular heart disease, cardiomyopathies, and congenital abnormalities, providing the detailed anatomical information that guides surgical and interventional planning. He is a faculty member of the European Association of Cardiovascular Imaging and regularly trains cardiologists from across Europe. He consults in Italian and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000029';

UPDATE doctor_profiles SET bio = 'Dr. Nadia Petrov is a dermatologist based in Moscow with eight years of clinical experience focusing on psoriasis, inflammatory skin conditions, and the emerging field of dermatology-rheumatology overlap syndromes, including psoriatic arthritis. She trained at Sechenov First Moscow State Medical University and completed subspecialty training in inflammatory dermatology at the University of Amsterdam''s Academic Medical Centre. Dr. Petrov was an early adopter of biologic therapies for severe psoriasis in Russia and has helped dozens of patients achieve remission after years of inadequate disease control with conventional treatments. She takes a meticulous, evidence-based approach to each case and stays at the forefront of rapidly evolving treatment guidelines through active participation in international dermatology congresses. She is known among her patients for her thoroughness and her genuine investment in their long-term quality of life. She consults in Russian and English.' WHERE user_id = 'a1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000030';

